<h3><i class="mch-search"></i> <img src="../../images/smart-1-1-magnifying-glass.jpg" alt="Image of Magnifying Glass" class="right ppic" />REVIEW. Aligning Learning with an Implementation Model</h3>

<h3>Implementation Model</h3>
    <p>As part of the Integrated Management of Childhood Illnesses (IMCI), a network of US-based non-governmental organizations (NGOs) convened between 1997-2001 and through multiple meetings and workshops developed a descriptive implementation framework for household and community integrated management of childhood illnesses. Utilizing three elements of action, this framework is easily adaptable to the MCH Leadership Competency: Systems Approach and is an ideal tool for describing, sharing and coordinating efforts in the field.<sup>1</sup></p>
	  <p> Topics are guided by <em>three elements of action</em>: (1) <strong>Improving partnerships</strong> between health facilities and the communities they serve, (2) <strong>Increasing promotion</strong> of appropriate and accessible health care and information from community-based providers, and (3) <strong>Integrating practices</strong> focused on families critical for maternal and child health.</p>
	 <p><img src="../../images/smart-implementation-framework-11.png"  alt="Implementation Framework" /></p>
